# TrustFlow deploy env template.
#
# This file is named `env.deploy.example` (no leading dot) on purpose. Copy it
# to `app/.env` (next to docker-compose.yml) and fill in the key:
#     cp deploy/env.deploy.example .env
# `app/.env` is git-ignored. NEVER commit a real key.
#
# With NO key set, the stack still boots and every S0x scenario runs via
# golden-transcript replay (?replay=S01..S05). The key is only needed for LIVE
# qwen-max negotiations.

# --- Required for LIVE negotiation (optional for replay-only demo) -----------
# DashScope (Alibaba) API key for the OpenAI-compatible endpoint.
DASHSCOPE_API_KEY=

# --- Optional overrides (sensible defaults baked into compose) ---------------
# Qwen OpenAI-compatible base URL. Default = Singapore/intl region, which the
# EU-region ECS box reaches and which the data-residency narrative assumes.
# QWEN_BASE_URL=https://dashscope-intl.aliyuncs.com/compatible-mode/v1

# Model id. Default in docker-compose is qwen-max (hackathon demo).
# For pay-as-you-go / free-quota dev, use qwen-flash on the intl endpoint:
# QWEN_MODEL=qwen-flash

# Backend log level (info | debug | warn | error).
# LOG_LEVEL=info

# --- Public access gate (shared passcode) ------------------------------------
# Set BOTH to require an HTTP basic-auth passcode on the whole site (recommended
# for the public ECS box so randoms can't burn your API budget). Share these
# with judges in your Devpost write-up. Leave BOTH unset to run open (local).
# BASIC_AUTH_USER=judge
# BASIC_AUTH_PASSWORD=pick-a-strong-shared-passcode
